  m_Name: Ulna_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Ulna_L
  partName: Ulna Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left ulna is located along the lateral aspect of the canine left forearm
    and works together with the radius to support forelimb movement and stability.
    It extends from the elbow joint to the carpal region and contains the olecranon
    process, which acts as a lever for muscles controlling elbow extension.
  - The ulna contributes to joint alignment, muscular attachment, and stabilization
    during weight-bearing activities. Although less involved in direct weight support
    than the radius, it remains essential for coordinated locomotion and efficient
    limb mechanics.
